      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): treat NO_REPLY-only turns as silent regardless of silence flag (#92038)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #92038.\n\nWhen the assistant replies with only the `NO_REPLY` token and no deliverable payloads, the embedded runner was treating it as an empty response. This triggered:\n\n1. Empty-response retry with visible-answer continuation\n2. Model-fallback cascade (`reason=format`) when retries also returned empty\n\nThis happened even though the assistant intentionally chose silence, particularly on heartbeat triggers where `allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent` defaults to `false`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/incomplete-turn.ts`: Added an early check in `shouldTreatEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent` to recognize deliberate silent-reply tokens (e.g. `NO_REPLY`) before consulting the `allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent` configuration flag.\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.incomplete-turn.test.ts`: Added unit tests covering:\n  - `NO_REPLY`-only turns are treated as silent even when `allowEmptyAssistantReplyAsSilent` is `false`\n  - `NO_REPLY` is **not** treated as silent when actual payloads are present\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.incomplete-turn.test.ts --run`: 120 tests passed (including 2 new ones)\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\n- Prevents unnecessary empty-response retries on heartbeat triggers when the assistant intentionally stays silent\n- Prevents model-fallback cascades triggered by `format` classification of intentionally empty payloads",
        "branch": "fix/no-reply-silence-empty-turn",
